text: Karanga may refer to: * Karanga (district), Mangaia, Cook Islands * Karanga (Māori culture), an element of Māori cultural protocol, the calling of visitors onto a marae * Karanga (Moshi Urban Ward), Old Moshi, Kilimanjaro Region, Tanzania * Karanga Chhota (village), a village in India * Karanga language, a Nilo-Saharan language spoken in Chad * Karanga people, a southern Bantu ethnic group * Karanga dialect * Ikalanga language, a Bantu language spoken in Botswana and Zimbabwe
title: Karanga
